title: Kiss Me Steph
description: Voula helps Stephanie in her campaign for school president, but is aghast when Stephanie tries to win votes by giving kisses to the boys.

title: The Big Dance
description: Voula lies to her father in order to go to the school dance. Stephanie, meanwhile, experiments with liquor, gets sick at the dance and has to leave her date behind.

title: The Experiment
description: Yick and Arthur copy someone else's essay as an experiment in fooling the teacher. Meanwhile, Melanie and Kathleen experiment with "drugs".

title: The Cover Up
description: Joey inadvertently helps his friend Rick when he discovers that Rick's dad beats him.

title: The Great Race
description: The girls from the swim team challenge the sexist boys on the soccer team to a swimming competition.

title: Rumor Has It
description: Many of Ms. Avery's students think that she is a lesbian. Caitlin, insists that her teacher isn't gay. After dreaming that her classmates think that she is also gay, Caitlin begins to act self-conscious at school.

title: The Best Laid Plans
description: 13 year-old Arthur plans to show his friends a pornographic video when his mother goes out on Friday night. Meanwhile older sister Stephanie makes plans to sleep with Wheels that same night. Their mother catches on to their plans just in time.

title: Nothing to Fear
description: When L.D.'s father goes into hospital, she is so terrified she cannot bring herself to visit him. Melanie, meanwhile, is afraid of the school snake which has disappeared from his cage.

title: What a Night
description: Lucy and Voula get picked up for shoplifting. Meanwhile, Stephanie is also in trouble after she meets her favorite soap star for a date.

title: Smokescreen
description: Rick joins the environmental action committee to impress Caitlin. Meanwhile, Yick would rather make up a family history for a project than tell the class he is a boat person.

title: It's Late
description: Spike, who is only 14 and suspects she is pregnant, turns to her girlfriends and finally her mother for help.

title: Parent's Night
description: Wheels is surprised by a visit from his birth father and has to deal with his feelings about being adopted. Meanwhile, 14 year-old Spike, who is pregnant, asks Wheels how it feels to be adopted.

title: Revolution
description: Stephanie learns the hard way to respect other people's feelings after the failure of her plan to make Wheels jealous.

title: Eggbert
description: Shane is afraid to tell his parents he's the father of Spike's baby. Meanwhile Spike learns about responsibility when she volunteers to "mother" an egg for two weeks.

title: A Helping Hand
description: Lucy needs a helping hand when her substitute teacher makes a pass at her.

title: Great Expectations
description: Arthur consults Dr. Sally, the phone-in sex expert, about his wet dreams. Meanwhile, Joey offends a girl he really likes by assuming she'll sleep with him.

title: Dinner and a Show
description: Shane's parents are upset and embarrassed that he is the father of Spike's baby. Nevertheless they invite Spike and her mother to dinner so everyone can meet and talk. Meanwhile Melanie is caught in a lie by Yick.

title: Stage Fright
description: Caitlin tries to hide her epilepsy from the other kids and even uses it as an excuse to get out of the school play. Meanwhile, Michelle chooses her speech topic - what it is like to be shy.

title: Fight!
description: Joey calls Dwayne dumb but soon lives to regret it. Meanwhile Stephanie does everything in her power to catch Simon's eye.

title: Bottled Up
description: Kathleen's alcoholic mother humiliates her the night she is to appear on a teen quiz show. Meanwhile, Max and Scooter think smoking is cool.

title: Sealed with a Kiss
description: The twins worry about mononucleosis after French kissing the same boy.

title: Dog Days
description: Arthur and Stephanie are both upset when their mother announces she's remarrying. Stephanie even mentions suicide.

title: Censored
description: Hearing that Spike may be kicked out of school for being pregnant, Caitlin writes a leaflet in her defense. Meanwhile Joey and L.D. get into trouble for having pinups in their lockers.

title: Trust Me
description: Snake lets Joey use his father's car. Meanwhile, Spike gets kicked out of school for being pregnant.

title: He's Back
description: Lucy tries to forget the bad experience she has had with her lecherous teacher Mr. Colby, until she sees him coming on to Susie.

title: Past Tense
description: It's the end of the school year and it is then announced that the eighth grade class will return to Degrassi in the fall, as the school is adding a ninth grade.

title: Can't Live with Them: Part 1
description: While out at Joey's place, Wheels is startled to come home and find out that both of his parents were killed by a drunk driver.

title: Can't Live with Them: Part 2
description: The whole school is stunned by the news of Wheel's parents.

title: A Big Girl Now
description: Lucy gets a bad reputation when the rumor spreads that she is sleeping with her boyfriend Paul.

title: Season's Greetings
description: Arthur and Yick have a falling out at Christmas time.

title: Loves Me, Loves Me Not
description: Caitlin has a big crush on Joey and agrees to work with him on a school project.

title: He Ain't Heavy
description: Snake learns his brother is gay.

title: The Whole Truth
description: Caitlin learns there are two sides to every story after writing an article for the school newspaper on animal experimentation.

title: Star-Crossed
description: Clutch uses the twins to get a date with Lucy. Meanwhile Wheels, still sensitive over the death of his parents, gets into a fight at school.

title: Food for Thought
description: Melanie discovers that Kathleen has an eating disorder.

title: Twenty Bucks
description: Melanie takes twenty dollars from her mother's purse to buy tickets to a rock concert. Meanwhile, Spike discovers Shane is reneging on child support so he can attend the rock concert.

title: Taking Off: Part 1
description: Wheels runs away from home. While hitchhiking, he is accosted by a strange man. Meanwhile, Shane disappears after taking LSD at a rock concert.

title: Taking Off: Part 2
description: Wheels visits his birth father after he runs away from home. Meanwhile, the police find Shane, who has disappeared after taking drugs at a rock concert.

title: Making Whoopee
description: Arthur resents it when his father begins dating.

title: Black & White
description: Michelle's parents won't let her go to the graduation dance with BLT because he is black. Spike is refused a job because of her punk haircut.

title: Pa-arty
description: Lucy throws a party while her parents are away. Meanwhile, Joey, Wheels and Snake get caught drinking under age.

title: Bye-Bye Junior High
description: Disaster strikes at the Degrassi Junior High graduation dance.

title: New Start: Part 1
description: Erica has missed her period and fears she may be pregnant.

title: New Start: Part 2
description: Erica decides to keep the pregnancy a secret, only telling Heather about it. She also decides to have an abortion; Heather disapproves of this, and this difference could tear the twins apart.

title: Breaking Up Is Hard to Do
description: Michelle discovers the complicated nature of divorce when her parents decide to go their separate ways.

title: Dream On
description: Arthur has a crush on Caitlin.

title: Everybody Wants Something
description: A hate campaign against Erica escalates, and Erica is determined to find out who is putting pro-life pamphlets and slogans on her locker.

title: Nobody's Perfect
description: Kathleen's new boyfriend begins to abuse her physically.

title: Just Friends
description: Heather has a crush on Wheels, and plans a party so that she'll have a chance to get closer to him.

title: Little White Lies
description: Diana is determined to grow up, and sneaks out to a party. Meanwhile Joey, Snake and Wheels decide it's time they expanded their horizons a little and attend a strip show.

title: Sixteen: Part 1
description: Michelle finds her father impossible to live with, but now that she's sixteen she can legally move out. Meanwhile Joey and Snake are excited about starting driving lessons.

title: Sixteen: Part 2
description: Alexa, the twins, and Lucy celebrate LD's 16th birthday with her in the hospital. Meanwhile Michelle tries to juggle school and a full-time job to pay for her rent.

title: All in a Good Cause
description: Caitlin and Claude want to do something to protest against a factory involved in nuclear missiles. Meanwhile Kathleen is stalked by her abusive ex-boyfriend Scott.

title: Natural Attraction
description: When Erica starts seeing a new boy, it frightens Heather. One abortion was bad enough, but what if she goes too far again?

title: Testing 1-2-3
description: Joey is diagnosed with dysgraphia.

title: It Creeps
description: Lucy becomes director and writer of her first film: a feminist horror flick starring the Zits, Simon and Caitlin, with Alexa, Tim and Heather as crew.

title: Stressed Out
description: Michelle starts taking caffeine pills to extend her study time. Meanwhile Caitlin is devastated when Ms Avery announces she is leaving Degrassi.

title: Bad Blood: Part 1
description: Dwayne receives a frightening phone call from his summer girlfriend. Meanwhile B.L.T. has trouble breaking up with Michelle.

title: Bad Blood: Part 2
description: Dwayne becomes increasingly withdrawn as he awaits the results of his HIV test. Meanwhile, Michelle finds out the real reason B.L.T. broke up with her.

title: Loyalties
description: Caitlin discovers her father is seeing another woman.

title: A Tangled Web
description: Caitlin becomes increasingly upset about her father's infidelity, but discovers that her mother already knows about it. Alex doesn't know what to do about his crush on Tessa.

title: Body Politics
description: Lucy takes a stand on behalf of the girl's volleyball team.

title: Crossed Wires
description: Liz begins to have repressed memories of being sexual abused as a child.

title: The All-Nighter
description: Melanie's surprise sleepover promises to hold more than one surprise when Kathleen finds some marijuana.

title: Home Sweet Home
description: Wheels wears out his welcome at Joey's house when he steals money from Mrs. Jeremiah.

title: Extracurricular Activities
description: Lucy, Heather and Erica hear the rumor that their favorite band, The Savages, are making a rock video at the school.

title: Show Time: Part 1
description: The whole school is thrown into turmoil when a student commits suicide at school - especially Caitlin, since the student is her ex-boyfriend, Claude.

title: Show Time: Part 2
description: Life begins to go on at Degrassi, but should they go through with Talent Night? Meanwhile, Caitlin begins to have nightmares about Claude's suicide.

title: Three's a Crowd
description: Snake invites Spike to the graduation formal, but then Michelle - who he'd really rather go with - invites him. What's a guy to do?

title: One Last Dance
description: The year's last dance takes on new significance when the news comes out. It's not just the year's last dance. It's Degrassi's last dance.
